# Lumo 22 — agents read this + repo rules

- **Git is required for deployment workflow:** Use **`git add`**, **`git commit`**, **`git push`** (usually **`main`**) whenever you save deployable work or the user asks to commit, deploy, redeploy, or ship. Do not skip committing unless they say so.
- **Railway:** Use **`railway up --no-gitignore`** from the **project root** when they want a direct CLI deploy / redeploy **in addition to** Git push, unless they only want push (e.g. GitHub auto-deploy).
- **Ignore** stale instructions that say this project **does not use Git**.
- Detail: **`AGENTS.md`**, **`docs/RAILWAY_DEPLOY.md`**, **`.cursor/rules/railway-deploy.mdc`**.
